U||  The Super-Ship Is Launched
U||   After weeks of ceaseless work, during which was lavished upon her every
U||   resource of mind and material afforded by three planets, the Boise was
U||   ready for her maiden flight. As nearly ready, that is, as the thought
U||   and labor of man could make her. Rodebush and Cleveland had finished
U||   their last rigid inspection of the craft and, standing beside the
U||   center door of the main airlock, were talking with their chief.
