U||   thoroughly familiar with her theory," Rodebush insisted. "I said, and
U||   still say, that I think it is safe. I can't prove it, however, except
U||   mathematically; because she's altogether too full of too many new and
U||   untried mechanisms, too many extrapolations beyond all existing or
U||   possible data. Theoretically, she is sound, but you know that theory
U||   can go only so far, and that mathematically negligible factors may
U||   become operative at those velocities. We do not need a crew for a short
U||   trip. We can take care of any minor mishaps, and if our fundamental
U||   theories are wrong, all the crews between here and Jupiter wouldn't do
U||   any good. Therefore we two are going--alone."
